##First-line female Doctor "ANTI-JAPANESE WAR" : meet physiological period is like a disaster

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Journalist, Zhong Xiaomei, intern, Shen Qingqing, thepaper.cn

It's not uncommon to wake up at 2:00 or 3:00 in the morning.

Touching his mobile phone, Li Xin sent a message to his friend: "What should I do if I'm nervous? You Comfort me. "

She's asleep. Of course she knows. It was only during the day that her nerves were released and the burden of the female doctor from the Hubei Medical Team of the Eastern Hospital affiliated to Tongji University was lifted. She began to worry about her daughter's study, her mother's diabetes and her own safety. The pent-up anxiety, fear, and loneliness came back.

Li Xin turns on his cell phone and pulls off his Hazmat suit. The demonstration doctor, who had fought against Zaire Ebolavirus, is now treating a critically ill new patient at Golden Pond Hospital. Every time the other person does it, she does it in her head until she goes to sleep.

The time of waking is not fixed. Other doctors get sick, fall over, shave their heads, scrape their skin, or don't find their gear... Li Xin gets a call from his temp any minute.

Wuhan East West Lake Shelter Hospital (also known as Wuhan Living Room Shelter Hospital) medical staff every six hours shift, 8 to 14 o'clock for the morning shift, followed by the afternoon shift, Middle Shift and night shift. The two shifts of each person are usually 24 to 48 hours apart.

The travel time, wearing off protective clothing, shift change and going back to the hotel to be disinfected, including these times, the medical staff had to be prepared two hours in advance, two hours to delay the rest. If Li Xin is on the early shift, he has to get up at 6 am. After her shift, she couldn't be in bed until 4:00 a.m.

In the dream, her blood was made into a specific vaccine, even the critically ill can be good. When the last patient was done grinning, the shelter was empty and the medical staff had gone home for the holidays.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A cartoon by Li Xin's daughter, hoping her mother will cure the new coronavirus. Unless otherwise noted, the pictures are provided for the interviewees

1
Equipment

1

Equipment

The morning alarm will wake Li Xin up at 6:00. The windows were blacked out, and there was no smoke or sirens in the walled city of Wuhan.

She used to call this room on the ninth floor of the east-west Lake District Hotel "home" : it made her feel safer than a shelter hospital.

"Home" no breakfast, in order to avoid the toilet and low blood sugar, she did not drink water, dry swallowed two small cakes.

Just in case, she has a small bottle of disinfectant and eye drops in her left pocket and a mask and antiviral solution in her right pocket. She tucks her clothes in, uses 20 hairpins to hold the hair in place, puts on a mask, slips on her galoshes, and heads downstairs.

At this time in Wuhan, the road is empty and cold, the doctors in the car sit together, can not help but "early to work" : A patient should have two days ago to do the nucleic acid test has been delayed, B patient because her husband died in the evening crying but against the psychologist, patient C wanted to see a CT scan, but the pod had to issue a results report..

Nearly 20 minutes later, the car stopped.

East West Lake Shelter Hospital 20 to 30 meters away, light-colored medical tents next to each other. A block away, the Golden Pool Hospital for critically ill patients overlooks the low-rise buildings.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As they entered the shelter, the staff felt the weight of the Golden Pool behind them: if the patient got sicker, he would soon be in more danger. Zhao Siweitu, reporter, thepaper.cn

Li Xin remembers that on Feb. 5, she and her colleagues spent more than three hours setting up the tents. At that time, the electrical and ventilation systems in the cabin were still under construction and there were no bulkheads. Looking at the crowded beds, she thought of a new coronavirus, scalp tingling.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There are beds everywhere in the shelter hospital.

The News of his death in the early hours of February 7 added to Li Xin's unease. That night, the East West Lake Shelter Hospital admitted patients, she was scheduled to enter the cabin in the early hours of February 8.

"want to go to war, suddenly nervous, in case I have what, daughter you take care of me, she do your daughter, I rest assured. " She sent a message to her daughter's head teacher.

She told her father the combination to her two bank cards and said she would leave the money for her daughter's school. "If the mother is not here, to take care of themselves, has been a teenager, the money to go to school with, do not spend. " She also told her daughter.

In the women's locker room tent, she put her phone in her locker, changed into her thin green scrubs, and ran against the cold toward the hatch.

East West Lake Shelter Hospital is divided into A, B, c three areas, each with a Hatchway, hatchway in front of all a tent. Five doctors and nearly 20 nurses went in to put on protective gear for each shift in each module.

At the beginning of the opening of the cabin, the protective articles are quite tight, and the medical staff have to adapt to the materials of different specifications. The Green Medical N95 mask was empty on the first day, leaving only the non-splash white N95 mask. In a few days, the face mask will become ear-hanging, and people like Li Xin, who have soft ears, will lose them. The leader is also anxious bad, contact a dairy company overnight took apart the handle of the milk carton, Hook the two ends of the handle with the mask strap fixed.

When Li Xin first arrived, there were no mirrors in the tent. She put on a mask, a surgical cap, a blue hazmat suit, a white hazmat suit, goggles, a face screen, gloves and a foot cap, following the steps she had memorized in her head. When she changed her mask, fearing cross contamination, she ran outside the tent, took a deep breath in the open, and put on a new one.

There's no way to check security, and she's afraid to go in. Thanks to a volunteer who had been a nurse, she had her hair cut and her mask and goggles checked for tightness.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Paramedics are putting on Hazmat suits. One of them had "spring is here" written on his shirt. Zhao Siweitu, reporter, thepaper.cn

Later, this tent set up a material manager. Some female nurses ear by mask rubber band cut skin, or forehead and nose by goggles, can find the administrator to "Ann Pu Paste. ". With this kind of water-glue dressing, the wound will not touch the sweat directly after entering the cabin and will not be infected.

You Liwen, a nurse in charge of material management, remembers that almost everyone who asks for "Haimps stickers" has a low voice and no confidence, as if asking for a "luxury item" . Surgical gloves that tighten the sleeves, high-quality boot covers, and extra-large protective clothing are all treasured by those who can receive them.

Once, a female nurse accidentally brought the N95 mask fell to the ground, staring at the ground, half a day did not ask again. You Liwen gave another one, the other side said several times thank you.

After about half an hour, the medics who had written their names on each other's suits entered the cabin one by one.

2
Battleground

2

Battleground

Through the last gate, Li Xin enters her battle field.

After the a cabin is full, the Hubei Medical Team of the Eastern Hospital affiliated to Tongji University is arranged to the B cabin, and the Hubei medical team of Ningxia, Guangdong, Xinjiang and other places will take classes together. Li Xin will be responsible for 115 patients per shift in Cabin B. Hall B. In addition, she will "package" 10 patients, off-duty when the telephone and Wechat to consult.

The clean-up area, the potential contamination area and the contamination area that she had passed before were three small rooms. The virus travels through convective air, so rooms can only be opened by one door.

Shift change is like a roller coaster, smooth communication of illness for a while, and suddenly received a thorny problem. A patient's husband died, she was crying, and the last doctor on call would have told her to call a therapist. One patient frantically demanded to know the results of the nucleic acid test, and she also needed to be comforted during rounds.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Xin's switching shifts with the last doctor.

At 8:20, Li Xin walked over to 918's bed and began rounds.

How long is the diagnosis? What's wrong with you? How many times did the nucleic acid and CT scan go through? How many days of medication do we have? Li Xin asked each patient the same question, writing it down on a piece of paper.

The patients woke up, saw Li Xin, and immediately sat up in bed. Whether it's a fever, diarrhea, chest tightness, lack of medication, or a mask worn for too long, nasal fever, snoring in the next bed affect sleep, patients will be detailed to Li Xin.

There's no cure for NCP, and most of the time, Li Xin's job is to take history and listen to relief.

"It's a weird virus, " Li Xin says, noting that many patients don't know who they've been infected with. A housewife told her that she went out to buy a bottle of vinegar. She didn't have intimate contact with anyone within one meter. She went home and began coughing.

As a cardiologist for 16 years, she found that heart rates were generally elevated in patients with new coronary pneumonia. She is responsible for 125 patients, twenty of whom have high blood pressure, diabetes and coronary heart disease, and she can make targeted diagnosis and treatment.

The beds were made by volunteers, and the white ones became colorful. Across the bed, a patient lifts the sheet and sticks his head out of a homemade curtain.

"excuse me Doctor, my heart beats very fast these two days, a little move on to 120 how to do? " A young girl can not help but "cut in line. ".

"Do you have hyperthyroidism? " Through his fogged goggles, Li Xin could faintly see the girl's bulging eyes.

The girl said she suffered from hyperthyroidism, but has not been reviewed for a year. Stress can trigger a relapse of hyperthyroidism, and Li Xin recommends that she take a heart rate lowering pill every day. The girl wanted to take a few days to ease up after the drug, Li Xin hurriedly advised "do not reduce, reduce the jump faster, discharged, family reunion again reduce, okay? "

A patient just checked in and asked how she was going to be discharged. A few other patients gathered quietly, waiting for Li Xin's answer.

In fact, the medical equipment in the shelter is gradually complete. In the beginning, there was only one mobile CT, capable of taking pictures of up to 30 patients a day, and the ship's doctor could only see the CT reports and could not access the images. Now, with the addition of a CT, the doctor can compare the film to determine the course of the disease. Rescue facilities also changed from a few oxygen cylinders, breathing machine, defibrillator, ECG monitoring and other complete equipment.

Li Xin explained that only a negative nucleic acid test could lead to a CT scan. After the normal CT results, patients can be discharged if the nucleic acid test is negative again and the course and symptoms meet the prescribed standards. There is a false negative rate for nucleic acid testing, and in some patients the results are often one negative and one positive. According to this discharge standard, patients need to be more patient.

"This is a temporary hospital, please understand, " Li Xin repeated.

3
"The past. "

3

"The past. "

In Li Xin's "battle plan, " about 1,400 patients are being discharged from the cabin and a new batch is being brought in. Three normal rounds like this, and the campaign will almost be won.

Dressed in an airtight protective suit, Li Xin sweats as he walks in a heated chamber at 24C. There are always patients at the back of the bed waiting to rush to wait, or previously checked patients come over to urge medicine. Some patients go to the office can not find her, fierce nurses and anxious to come over to ask the results.

It's hard to hear with a mask on, and some patients like to whisper in Li Xin's ear. There was a risk of infection by getting too close, and Li Xin pulled away, speaking loudly, wrapped in protective clothing. The mouth becomes drier and drier, and the skin on your lips feels a tug when you keep talking. Masks and goggles cover the nose and breath through the mouth, drying the mouth.

He's got all this gear, like a chain around his neck.

The rubber band on her face mask wasn't pulled over her head, and she was slipping as she walked. She couldn't touch it with her hands, so she kept her head stiff. Goggles are so tight, they're cutting off oxygen to the brain. You can't wipe a runny nose. It won't hang. Give it another sniff.

It happens all the time. Some nurses even have to pee blood because they have to pee for so long. Surrounded by patients and other medics, Li Xin was embarrassed to pee even in a diaper, afraid of his suit breaking and afraid to squat. Really hold back, Lixin will pass the partition when standing a urine.

When the Menstrual period, female medical staff "like a hijack. ". Menstrual blood uncontrolled flow to the sanitary Napkin, usually 3 to 4 hours can be replaced once, into the shelter before and after nearly 10 hours, blood leakage to safety pants. He walked as if he had worn a pair of sticky and bloody trousers.

Nurses are sometimes busier than doctors, handing out pills to patients, handling doctor's orders, checking in and out of hospitals, keeping track of patients'lack of shampoo and other trivia. Not to eat, not to drink physical exhaustion, coupled with dysmenorrhea, had menstrual period of the nurse fainted in the cabin.

Three hours later, after the last patient had said "thank you, Dr. Lee, " Li Xin went back to his office and sat down to fill out the prescription.

Goggles fog, besmear bath liquid, iodophor disinfection liquid also can not last long, can only 360 degrees turn to look for the corner without fog. Looking at a computer screen is even more dizzying.

Li Xin catalogued the prescriptions, tests, and medical complaints collected during rounds. With two layers of gloves on his fingers, and sweat on his fingers, typing became painful.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Xin from rounds.

Patients who are absent during rounds will be brought in to fill in. Many patients like Hoida, and they pass by their desks and ask Li Xin for the results of a test. The nurse would lead the patient through the breathing drill, distracting them, and the "rescued" Li Xin would seize the moment and knock on the doctor's orders.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Xin is typing doctor's orders on the computer. There was a bottle of water on the table for the patient to drink. Li Xin quipped, "all we see is alcohol, no water. " .

Once a patient stood at the door of her office and called her "Dr. Lee" from a distance. The aunt's relatives were quarantined, leaving only two people over 85 at home. Because there was only enough refills in the insulin pen for two days, I had no choice but to ask her for help. Afraid of passing the virus on to her, would rather talk loudly from a distance.

"She had no choice but to come to me, so I had to do everything I could to help her, " said Li Xin, whose mother is also diabetic and does not suffer from insulin-induced ketoacidosis. Before she left, she told her mother to stock up on medicine for a few months before she left.

There were not many diabetics in the shelter hospital. She asked the medical team all over the shelter and called the drug dispatcher. After two days, she found a matching pencil refill for her aunt. Later, she transferred her aunt to a designated hospital.

"congratulations, you're out of the hospital. " Shortly before 11 o'clock, the name of five people rang out on the cabin radio. All the patients clap together. Li Xin heard a patient in her ward inside, and asked the nurse to wait for her to bring her discharge papers.

When she returned, there was nothing on the bed but the woman's Brown down jacket. "It's like running for my life, " Li Xin said, beaming like a victorious general.

4
Outbursts

4

Outbursts

Any time something unexpected comes up.

The shelter was as bright as day in the dead of night. On the day of Li Xin's first shift, the community was delivering patients to the shelter in the early hours of the morning. The Shelter Hospital made a temporary decision to let all the patients sleep in the cabin first, and then make up the hospitalization procedures and medical advice the next day. Li Xin was in hall a, the closest to the aisle, and within an hour of patients entering the empty bed, more than 180 people had been admitted to her ward.

At 2:35 a.m. , a patient in room a, bed 24, suddenly started breathing Oxygenation, dropping to 89 percent.

Li Xin's back broke into a cold sweat. Office wall contact phone, she called one by one, referral phone busy tone, finally got through to the dispatch phone, but the other side said that the evening can not refer patients.

He ran back to the patient's bed, where he was too winded to lie down. "there was no way to resuscitate him, " Li Xin recalled. There were no oxygen tanks or breathing machines in the cabin, and CPR was the only way to resuscitate him in case he didn't make it. She stood there like a soldier without a bullet.

A matron on a night tour "saved" her.

A 100 pounds of blue oxygen bottle, was the head nurse from the extravehicular rescue room all the way to the patient bed. By 3:30, they were able to give the patient oxygen. Half an hour later, when the patient's Oxygenation had risen to 94 percent, Li Xin was relieved.

In bed 36, the patient's temperature rose to 39.9 °C, and Li Xin was back on a tight leash. At that time, many drugs could not be obtained in time, so they had to be physically cooled and cold towels applied to the forehead. Li Xin waited until the 22 year old's temperature dropped before leaving.

Shouting, crying is also a kind of alarm.

There was a psychiatrist in the ward with a new case of coronary pneumonia, shouting excitedly. Seeing her and the other two doctors, the man "plopped" down on his knees to them, threw out two medical certificates, said he did not have a fever but tested positive for nucleic acid, crying that he was not ill, and asked to leave the cabin.

For the next two days, though he still did not think he had new pneumonia, he gradually accepted life in the cabin.

A woman who had lost her husband burst into tears at night. When Li Xin arrived, the woman's hair was in a tangle and tears were dripping into her mask. Her roommate handed her a tissue, and the woman didn't reach for it. Li Xin asked her if she wanted a drink of water.

"want to cry cry to cry. " Li Xin sticks in that, listens to the woman to cry to shout. Her husband, suffering from severe new pneumonia, died in the opposite hospital, she even did not see the last one.

After 20 minutes, the woman, tired of crying, put her head under the covers and showed an eye. Seeing the woman close her eyes, Li Xin walked away. In the latter part of the night, when she went on Tiptoe, the woman was fast asleep. The next day the psychologist Feng Qiang into the cabin to ask, the woman cried to him, but has not admitted that her husband died.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sunset outside the shelter.

In his panic, Li Xin's shoe cover had fallen off once in the cabin. Such "streaking" can be fatal. She stood where she dare not go, a nurse in Ningxia saw, quickly go to the office to bring her alcohol emergency disinfection, find a medical waste bag on emergency.

Everyone agrees that taking off a Hazmat suit is more rigorous than wearing it. The medical personnel passage out of the cabin is divided into buffer zone, one-off compartment, two-off compartment and three-off area. Two guards at the exit, two at a time.

Li Xin waited for more than two hours in line behind the nurses who had gathered to exit the capsule.

There were no lights in the buffer zone and it was pitch black. To prevent the Aerosol spreading the virus, one had to stand for a quarter of an hour before entering one of the cells.

Do it slowly, do it in the wrong order, and danger will come. The medical waste bins are piled high with so much garbage. Li Xin could only hold her breath as she approached. In the case of hand sanitizer, face mask was taken, the person is equivalent to be "stuck" , can not return to the more polluted areas, can not bring the virus to the clean area.

Most impressively, Li Xin stood there for half an hour waiting for the supervisor to bring her surgical mask. The door of Santuo district was open, the wind poured in, and she shivered with cold after taking off her protective clothing.

5
Wheezing

5

Wheezing

Under pressure, Li Xin occasionally chats with the crew and relaxes outside.

Most of the patients were asleep during the night shift. On the days when there was no heat, Li Xin sat down on a stool next to the electric heater and dozed a little.

Wuhan Snow that day, colleagues in the group said, "cold to remember tim clothes. ". Li Xin put on her thermal underwear, but the heat in the cabin turned up so hot that she was wet with sweat. "It felt like she was going to evaporate. ". She went out through the patient tunnel to get some air.

On the left side of the door is the toilet, on the right side is the washstand, and in the middle is the open-air Walkway. It was a quiet night, and two male cleaners saw her and helped her move a chair.

"You are very hot now, don't talk, sit down, " they said, seeing that Li Xin had written "Hubei daughter-in-law" on her body. They made small talk with her, said "thank you for coming to Wuhan" and left.

Huang Wei was born in 1990 and worked as a cleaner for the urban management and Law Enforcement Bureau in the east-west Lake District of Wuhan. He and his colleagues work more than four hours a day cleaning 10 to 12 tons of excrement to keep it from overflowing.

"The smell of feces pierced through the mask, which seemed to magnify the strong odor and only made people nauseous, " Huang said, putting up with the smell of "immortality. " Under the restraint of protective clothing disinfection, lift water pipe, suck excrement.

Protective clothing is not waterproof, but toilet flushing, disinfection have to deal with water. You can also get urine on your body when you suck shit. Although heard that the virus may be transmitted through faecal mouth, but Huang Wei felt that there is no need to be too afraid or care about these things, "doctors are brave in front of it. ".

On his way back from the hatch, Li Xin wandered around, and occasionally saw the guards guarding the entrance and exit crouching and nodding against the wall.

Cao Huai should belong to the people who could not go home because of the "closure of the city" . The 35-year-old and his colleagues signed up from the company dormitory after seeing the information about the shelter hospital's recruitment for security.

"Just like at home, there are things you can not finish. " During the six-hour shift, Cao Huai should sometimes transport supplies, sit guard at the gate, bored to change the Water Dispenser Bucket.

One patient quarreled because he could not stand the sight of another pouring water into a ditch where wires were buried. The man next to him shouted, "people from all sides will come to support us. If we quarrel again, WE WILL LOSE WUHAN'S FACE! " He saw this and quickly pulled the two men back to his bed.

Dialect was the thing that bothered him the most. There were many old people in the shelter. Once, an old lady asked him for something from his family, but he didn't receive it. The Old Lady did not understand his mandarin, spoke a dialect, followed him after a half hour to leave.

Most of the time, Cao Huaiying will receive a "thank you, hard" , feel that their volunteers is not in vain, "at least others know you hard, know you tired.

It was a pleasure for Li Xin to get out of the cabin tired.

The air was so fresh outside, I went back to the hotel and took off my mask and drank the half bottle of coke I had left when I left. For a moment, it felt good to be alive and healthy.

When she wasn't on duty, she would write about her work, and when she got tired, she would do Jung Da-yeon's weight loss exercises in her room. Look at the Basketball Court under the hotel and imagine what it would be like to run around it. Some of the nurses were dancing in the next room, showing her videos of the shaking. The door was open and everyone could stand in front of their room and talk with their masks on.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Looking out of the hotel window, the football and basketball courts look particularly "inviting" .

On his first day in Wuhan, Li Xin, who had been working the day before, had no time to go home and pack, except for a suitcase sent by the medical team. One by one, the community donated more and more materials, Li Xin's room more nail scissors, biscuit cake, shampoo, Sanitary Napkins, hot water bag.

"The food at home is quite complete, I feel I can with the opposite canteen boss PK, " Li Xin said.

Her biggest concern was her daughter's education. In her mind, fourth grade was a watershed. In the class group, many parents who do not work outside the home have issued guidance and supervision schedules for their children's learning.

"I've been home for three months on vacation, and I feel like my daughter is losing and falling behind because someone is staring at her every day. " The family's elderly can't control their children, and their husband is being quarantined after he returns from a trip. In the dead of night, she became an ordinary parent, sleeping in anxiety.

The time to wake up again is still fluid. Sure enough, when she wakes up, she'll be back in the shelter.

On the Lantern Festival, the father sent Li Xin a photo of his daughter with Li Xin.
